<br>
I can think of some possible reasons why it isn't/hasn't been done, but for now I'll leave the request open.   <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=243103">Xenjuro</A> of <A HREF="http://www.tritonguild.com">Triton</A>, Povar</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukydaan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kydaan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/15/02 6:44:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=288.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Let us be able to see Avoidance and Mitigation AC number</span><hr size=1> With the customisations that are possible in the new UI, how about just adding in two new tags for avoidance AC and mitigation AC.  Leave the default UI the same as it is now (i.e. don't put the new tags in to the default UI) so nobody can be confused by the numbers that may appear but allow UI customizations that put both numbers up on the screen if the person wants to.  If you're sophisticated enough to be changing the UI, you're probably not going to be confused by the extra numbers. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucybsled.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cybsled</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Master</span><br>  Posts: 1070<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/15/02 11:17:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=288.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Well</span><hr size=1> In beta you could view both, but for some reason VI thought that was too hard for the average gamer to comprehend so they mashed them all into one number.<br>
<br>
I think alot of problems could have been avoided by reintroducing the two numbers.  The numbers still exist, we just cant see them seperated. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uleewei.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leewei</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 175<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/15/02 11:59:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=288.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well</span><hr size=1> From what I understand, Avoidance Factor is derived from the following:<br>
<br>
-Character class<br>
-Defense skill<br>
-AAxp skills<br>
-Character level(?)<br>
<br>
Mitigation Factor is derived from:<br>
<br>
-Character class<br>
-Agility<br>
-Armor<br>
-Buffs<br>
-Character race<br>
-Character level(?)<br>
<br>
The effect of Agility is believed to be close to negligible, since this only appears to slightly modify AC.  Racial factor and Agility modifier to AC are pretty well documented on this site, I believe.  Next time you're on a corpse run, you can check your AC.  Subtracting racial and Agility factors out, you should have something close to pure avoidance AC.  The difference between this and your standard AC with gear is certainly purely mitigation AC.<br>
<br>
AC is only half the mystery, though.  ATK has some values as well which determine how frequently and how hard a character hits.<br>
<br>
I have other questions as well.  Do Block / Dodge / Riposte fire off as often against all opponents, or less often against a skilled attacker?  From the looks of it, these skills work at a set rate, but might not prevent Flurry attacks.<br>
<br>
At the moment, I am guessing that hit is determined randomly from Hit-ATK and Avoid-AC, then damage is applied from Penetrate-ATK and Mitigate-AC.  In between, each defensive skill is checked.  Also a guess -- defense skills probably work using a chance with a straight ratio to the skill level.  Block, for instance, may work Block_skill x 0.1% of the time (i.e. 25.2% of the time at a skill of 252). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucybsled.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cybsled</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Master</span><br>  Posts: 1073<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/16/02 1:38:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=288.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Er</span><hr size=1> Actually agility counts towards avoidance ac.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulyndar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lyndar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 240<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/16/02 6:38:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=288.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Er</span><hr size=1> I second the motion, please allow us to see both avoidance and mitigation ac. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=291578"><IMG SRC="http://lyndar.netfirms.com/sigpic.JPG" ALIGN=center></a><BR>Grandmaster<BR>Bristlebane</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=crouchingtiger>crouchingtiger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/16/02 6:44:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=288.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ..</span><hr size=1> i agree, why cant the advanced users be able to see the number? we pay money to play on their shitty servers, we should know what the hell is going on. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubeldryn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Beldryn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 114<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/16/02 6:59:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=288.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ..</span><hr size=1> to hell with that i say put it in the default UI as standard, i dont use a custom UI cause i dont give a crap enough to go messing with it, so i say put it in the defualt one and give it an option to be turned off or something. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=382017 target=_blank>Brother Beldryn Dragonfist</a><BR>
